I served at the &quot;Bridge Ramp&quot; NSA Da Nang 68-69.  I have found little in Naval history pages but the Marines had an article about Naval Support Activites and what they did in aiding Grunts in one of there history periodicals. But there is very little Naval History beyound &quot;SEALs, River Boats or 7th Fleet.  Along with a lot of you, I feel that the Navy just conciders us less important then &quot;Glory Boys&quot; and as usual taken us for granted. If you were like me you did a lot of hump-en and a lot of dodge-en.  Many of you that were in the DA Nang area in 68 &amp; 69 remember what it was like and all the shots we took at the river, Freedom Hill, Camp Tenchau, Monkey Mountain, and Marble Mountain.  If you want to read about this time look up Marine Corp History and find the &quot;Battle of Da Nang&quot;.  The Corp did a good job of recording the action that took place in 69.<br><br>

